<http://dx.doi.org/10.1080/00222933.2016.1145272>
    bibo:endPage "1612" ;
    bibo:issue "25" ;
    bibo:journal "Journal of Natural History" ;
    bibo:startPage "1583" ;
    bibo:volume "50" ;
    dc:creator "Felipe N. Soto-Adames" ;
    dc:date "2016" ;
    dc:title "Chaetotaxy of first-instar Campylothorax sabanus (Wray), and description of three new Campylothorax species from Hispaniola (Collembola, Paronellidae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.269884>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.269885>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.269886>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.269883> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.269884>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Campylothorax notidanus sp. nov. habitus. (A) Dark individual. (B) Detail of light-coloured individual. (C) Dorsal view of fourth abdominal segment of light-coloured individual." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/269884/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.269885>
    dc:description "Figure 5. Campylothorax notidanus sp. nov. (A) Dorsal chaetotaxy of head. (B) Maxilla. (C) Detail of maxillar lamella 1. (D) Labrum; pps = proximal pleural chaeta; dps = distal pleural chaeta. (E) Outer maxillary lobe. (F) Labial papilla E. (G) Labial chaetotaxy. (H) Thorax and first abdominal segment; arrow points anteriorly. (I). Chaetotaxy of second abdominal segment." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/269885/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.269886>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Campylothorax notidanus sp. nov. (A). Chaetotaxy of third abdominal segment. (B) Hind claw complex. (C) Chaetotaxy of fourth abdominal segment. (D) Hind claw, dorsal (anterior) view. (E) Mucro." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/269886/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.269883>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Campylothorax sabanus dorsal chaetotaxy of fourth and fifth abdominal segments. (A) Fourth abdominal segment, first instar. (B) Fourth abdominal segment adult. (C) Detail of postero-lateral chaetotaxy of adult fourth abdominal segment in a different individual. (D) Alternative hypothesis of homology for inner and lateral Mc in adults. (E) Fifth abdominal segment, first instar. (F) Fifth abdominal segment, adult." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/269883/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

